line_1: Deep waters darkly silent roll.
line_2: A truer sorrow sways my soul;

line_1: O save me, save me, ere the thunders roll,
line_2: And hell's black caverns swallow up my soul.

line_1: Vast peals of thunder o'er the ocean roll,
line_2: The flame-wing'd lightning gleams from pole to pole.

line_1: These please not me — Bright Eyes in vain may roll,
line_2: I read no Charms but in the purer Soul.

line_1: Such jarring Tumults in your Bosom roll;
line_2: (Ah, what so various as a Woman's Soul!)

line_1: In every Liquid there's a constant Rowl;
line_2: An Eddy, tho' unseen, disturbs the whole.

line_1: Far as thou bad'st Britannia's thunder roll.
line_2: And glowing health support thy active soul;

line_1: Or Waves which through that wond'rous City roll.
line_2: Rest then content, my too impatient Soul;

line_1: Who measured out the year and bade the seasons roll;
line_2: How the rude surge its sandy bounds control;

line_1: What sends yon fleet o'er boist'rous seas to roll,
line_2: Beneath the burning line, and frozen pole?

line_1: Not bubbling waters as they roll,
line_2: Can tranquillize his bursting soul,

line_1: But still those eyes that wildly roll,
line_2: Bespeak the tempest in his soul.

line_1: Why in our Sight those shining Wonders roll?
line_2: Or why to Man was giv'n a thinking Soul?

line_1: How great the Pow'r, who gave those Worlds to roll;
line_2: The Thought strikes inward, and confounds the Soul;

line_1: Made gentler constellations roll,
line_2: 'Till letter'd Athens round the pole

line_1: True, from his eyes no streams of anguish roll,
line_2: His burning tears fall inwards on his soul:

line_1: How Orbs o'er Orbs in mystic Dance should roll,
line_2: What Laws support, and regulate the Whole:
